      • loadFromOBOFile

        public static Ontology loadFromOBOFile(String oboFilePath,
                                       String shortName,
                                       String fullName,
                                       String definition)
                                throws IOException
        Facade method to simplify most of the Loader package code for user who simply want to obtain a fully-constructed ontology object from a single OBO source file. This method will produce an object that is still valid for persistence however, so mandatory fields need to be provided.
        Parameters:
        oboFilePath - - The fully qualified path to the file on disk to be parsed [Mandatory]
        shortName - - The short label of the ontology (eg "GO", "MI", etc...) [Mandatory]
        fullName - - The full name of the ontology (eg Gene OntologyAccess) [Optional]
        definition - - The definition of the ontology [Optional]
        Returns:
        a fully build OntologyAccess object.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the shortName is null or an empty string
        IOException - on parse errors

      • loadFromOBOFile

        public static Ontology loadFromOBOFile(URL oboFileURL,
                                       String shortName,
                                       String fullName,
                                       String definition)
                                throws IOException
        Facade method to simplify most of the Loader package code for user who simply want to obtain a fully-constructed ontology object from a single OBO source file that is accessed via an URL. The URL can be local or remote. If the URL is remote, a temporary copy will be obtained and parsed. This method will produce an object that is still valid for persistence however, so mandatory fields need to be provided.
        Parameters:
        oboFileURL - - The URL of the OBO file to be read (remote or local) [Mandatory]
        shortName - - The short label of the ontology (eg "GO", "MI", etc...) [Mandatory]
        fullName - - The full name of the ontology (eg Gene OntologyAccess) [Optional]
        definition - - The definition of the ontology [Optional]
        Returns:
        a fully build OntologyAccess object.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the shortName is null or an empty string
        IOException - if the URL cannot be read or on parse errors

      • loadFromOBOFile

        public static Ontology loadFromOBOFile(File oboFile,
                                       String shortName,
                                       String fullName,
                                       String definition)
                                throws IOException
        Facade method to simplify most of the Loader package code for user who simply want to obtain a fully-constructed ontology object from a single OBO source file. This method will produce an object that is still valid for persistence however, so mandatory fields need to be provided.
        Parameters:
        oboFile - - The File object to be parsed [Mandatory]
        shortName - - The short label of the ontology (eg "GO", "MI", etc...) [Mandatory]
        fullName - - The full name of the ontology (eg Gene OntologyAccess) [Optional]
        definition - - The definition of the ontology [Optional]
        Returns:
        a fully build OntologyAccess object.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the shortName is null or an empty string
        IOException - on parse errors
